    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue Trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/77"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Einricus</persName> gratia Dei <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. «Certum est quia quanto magis sanctorum
                        ecclesias et honorem ampliabimus, tanto largius eorum subsidia et Dei
                        remuneracionem impetrabimus». Noverit igitur omnium fìdelium nostrorum
                        diligencia, tam futurorum quam qui in nostra modo sunt presencia, quod nos,
                        ideo et ob peticionem quidem nostre care genitricis <persName
                            ref="#people/365" key="#Queen">Agnetis</persName> et <rs key="#Queen"
                            >imperatricis</rs> auguste et <persName key="#Chancellor"><name
                                ref="Gubertus">Guiberti</name></persName> dilecti nostri <rs
                            key="#Chancellor">cancellarii</rs>, <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/53" key="#Monasteries">Sanctorum Systi et
                            Fabiani et Sancte Resurectionis</orgName>, quod est constructum infra
                            <rs key="#Walls">menia</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/43" key="#Cities #Walls">Placentine</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">urbis</rs>, precepto nostre confirmacionis concedimus
                        atque permittimus quicquid modo legaliter detinet vel in antea Deo adiuvante
                        adquirere poterit, et nominatim sicut <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >ager</rs>
                        <geogName ref="#estates/1524"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/1934"
                                key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Corni</placeName></geogName> et <geogName ref="#estates/1523"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/612"
                                key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Lardarie</placeName></geogName> ad alterutrum extenditur et sicut
                            <rs key="#Rivers"><placeName ref="#places/2308 #places/4196"
                                >Padus</placeName></rs> et <placeName ref="#places/1981"
                            >Adua</placeName> ab hinc discurunt quousque simul conveniunt; ita
                        permittimus atque concedimus omnem <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs> ad
                            <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> predicti monasterii que est <rs
                            key="#Islands">insula</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/1935"
                            key="#Islands #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/1525"
                                key="#Islands #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus"
                                >Runcarioli</geogName></placeName>, quatinus omnes habitantes vel
                        hos intra terminos proprium aliquid habentes a deinceps solummodo ante
                        predicti monasterii <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatissam</rs> vel aliquam personam
                        ab ea missam perficiant ex ipso suo proprio omne <rs
                            key="#Seigneurial_district">placitum</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Profits_of_justice">emendacionem</rs> et ipsi monasterio vel
                        abbatisse persolvant omnes <rs key="#Public_exactions">publicas actiones et
                            functiones cum omni excuvio</rs>, sicut nobis debent vel nostro <rs
                            key="#Count">comiti</rs> aut nostro <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missatico</rs>;<rs
                            key="#Teloneum"> toloneum</rs> quoque et curaturam et <rs key="#Markets"
                            >mercata</rs> vel etiam omnia que sunt ad publicum regium pertinencia
                        habeat deinceps ipsius monasterii omnis abbatissa; ipsa etiam flumina paulo
                        ante nominata, a quo et quousque ea supra determinavimus, sua similiter
                        sint, ut habeat in eis universas <rs key="#Fisheries">piscaciones</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Ports">portum</rs> et <rs key="#Tolls">repaticum</rs>,
                        cuiuscumque sint terre, atque confinia et palificatura et omnia in integrum
                        quecumque ad nostrum pertinent opus publicum, excepta <rs key="#Gold"
                            >auri</rs> lavacione, quam <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere</rs>
                        reservavimus nostre. Concedimus etiam et per hoc preceptum confirmamus ut
                        nullus <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux, marchio</rs>, comes, <rs key="#Viscount"
                            >vicecomes</rs>, nulla magna parvaque nostri regni persona predictum
                        monasterium de omnibus supradictis inquietare aut molestare presumat. Si
                        quis autem huius nostri precepti violator extiterit, sciat se compositurum
                            <rs key="#Penalty">tercentum libras auri</rs>, medietatem camere nostre
                        et medietatem predicto monasterio. Quod ut cercius credatur et firmius
                        habeatur, nostri sigilli impressione iussimus insigniti. (Signum) domni
                        Einrici quarti regis * * *,invictissimi : : <persName key="#Chancellor"
                                ><name ref="Sigelbertus">Sigelbertus</name></persName> cancellarius
                        vice <persName ref="#people/1306" key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops"
                            >Annonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi : Data pridie kalendas novembris anno
                        incarnacionis Domini .mlxj., indicione .xv., anno ordinacionis Einrici
                        quarti regis .viij., regni vero eius .vj. Actum Scuchino, feliciter
                        amen.</ab>
                </div>
